// @check
// @error-at 6:5 A type alias requires a body; write `type Bar = …` to define `Bar`
// A bodyless `type Bar` (no `= body`) is reported AT THE DECLARATION with a clear,
// actionable message that names the alias and shows the fix — not a downstream
// "refers to itself" error at the use site. Opaque/recursive aliases are
// unsupported today (ROADMAP A14); the `= { … }` form is how you declare a type.
type Bar
let y: Bar = 0
